  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add cumin seeds, mustard seeds, fenugreek seeds, and a pinch of asafoetida, sauté until seeds crackle and emit a nutty aroma.",
    "Pour in tomato puree and cook for 3 minutes, stirring to blend the spices.",
    "Add the coconut milk, okra, tamarind mixture, red chili flakes, paprika, saffron water and the soaked saffron strands. Stir well.",
    "Add water, bring the mixture to a gentle simmer and cover. Let it cook for 15 minutes, until the okra is tender and the flavors meld.",
    "Stir in the chopped rocket, lemon juice, and black pepper. Cook uncovered for an additional 5 minutes, allowing the rocket to wilt but retain its bite.",
    "Transfer the stew to a serving bowl. Sprinkle the crushed roasted cashew nuts over the surface, giving it a flaky, nutty crust.",
    "Serve hot, ideal for a midnight craving. Pair with crusty bread or a side of quinoa for a complete meal."
  ],
